1
00:00:08,174 --> 00:00:09,175
It's all your fault.

2
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,811
Your actions caused misunderstandings.

3
00:00:11,811 --> 00:00:13,513
Even I, when I look at them…

4
00:00:13,513 --> 00:00:14,714
What?

5
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:18,351
Look, it's like this.

6
00:00:19,386 --> 00:00:21,321
Should we explain?

7
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:22,689
Explain what?

8
00:00:24,424 --> 00:00:26,893
Or do you not want to make it public?

9
00:00:31,798 --> 00:00:34,267
I didn't expect we could
see a real-life love scene.

10
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,002
This is so exciting.

11
00:00:36,002 --> 00:00:37,437
Sorry to interrupt.

12
00:00:39,005 --> 00:00:40,874
Hello, we're from the school newspaper.

13
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,576
Since everyone is very curious about you two,

14
00:00:43,576 --> 00:00:45,145
can we have an interview with you?

15
00:00:45,145 --> 00:00:46,546
- Sure.
- Not really.

16
00:00:50,016 --> 00:00:51,918
There were rumors that you two
were not getting along.

17
00:00:51,918 --> 00:00:53,586
Is that true?

18
00:00:54,187 --> 00:00:55,680
Yes.

19
00:00:56,756 --> 00:00:57,891
Why?

20
00:00:58,458 --> 00:01:00,226
Because he didn't want to live with others.

21
00:01:00,827 --> 00:01:03,096
Then how did you two make up?

22
00:01:03,096 --> 00:01:05,865
You seem to get along
very well from the photos.

23
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:11,504
I just saw the photos this morning.

24
00:01:11,504 --> 00:01:12,972
I realized our schoolmates

25
00:01:13,807 --> 00:01:15,675
are really good at taking photos.

26
00:01:16,843 --> 00:01:18,545
Sorry, I digressed.

27
00:01:19,145 --> 00:01:22,082
This is a good chance to clarify

28
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:24,651
that our relationship is actually quite good.

29
00:01:24,651 --> 00:01:26,653
He might have a cold and serious face,

30
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:28,388
but actually, he's a good person.

31
00:01:28,388 --> 00:01:30,390
Although I was very annoyed with him at first,

32
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:31,825
later I found out

33
00:01:31,825 --> 00:01:34,194
he was cold on the outside
but warm on the inside.

34
00:01:34,194 --> 00:01:36,196
Are you two dating?

35
00:01:41,901 --> 00:01:43,436
We're just together.

36
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:51,778
We just live together.

37
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,114
Can you define a specific timing

38
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:56,883
of liking someone?

39
00:01:59,352 --> 00:02:00,854
For me,

40
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:03,256
there's no specific timing for liking someone.

41
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,259
When you can't stop thinking about someone,

42
00:02:06,259 --> 00:02:08,061
that's probably when you start to like him.

43
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:20,473
Buxia, what about you?

44
00:02:21,341 --> 00:02:22,475
- I…
- Right.

45
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,477
The reason why I joined the basketball team…

46
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:27,113
Was it for Buxia?

47
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:35,188
Please cheer for the basketball team together.

48
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:37,690
- So you two later…
- That's all the questions.

49
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:38,791
I haven't finished yet.

50
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:39,959
Thank you. We'll leave now.

51
00:02:39,959 --> 00:02:41,794
I still have questions.

52
00:02:42,795 --> 00:02:43,997
Wait.

53
00:02:45,598 --> 00:02:47,834
Why did you say that?

54
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,203
Isn't it good to cheer for the basketball team?

55
00:02:50,904 --> 00:02:52,205
No.

56
00:02:52,205 --> 00:02:54,574
It's the way you said it and that expression,

57
00:02:54,574 --> 00:02:56,709
